edyyyyyy yes a gooood national podium oration the village money barn the true formula of social justice by edy mustaat son of banyuwangi descendant of mbah buyut ponorogo badegan bandar alim chapter i the awakening my brothers and sisters of this great nation i stand here today not seek fame but awaken the conscience of our people the heart and soul of indonesia the villages for too long our people have paid waited and hoped they pay taxes electricity bills water bills phone credits and property dues every payment made with sweat and struggle but where does all that money go flows upward into central accounts and high offices while the villages the true roots of this nation remain poor and forgotten enough is enough is time bring the peoples money back where the people live the villages chapter ii the flame of justice from the sacred land of banyuwangi from the ancient spirit of ponorogo badegan bandar alim i edy mustaat declare one formula of justice establish a village money barn every village of indonesia every village must have its own financial barn a place collect and manage all payments from its citizens all public payments property tax vehicle tax water electricity internet phone credits import duties must be paid at the village office because all those services exist and operate within village territory villages must distribute the funds wisely and flexibly and we must understand that this nation stands on a hierarchy of leadership village head police head military sector head district commander regency head governor and the head of state the president of the republic of indonesia from this logic we rediscover the true structure where salaries of civil servants soldiers airmen and police must be rooted again the economic strength of the villages and listen carefully if purbabaya orang rocky gerung orang any national thinker refuse respect and adopt this formula then mark these words article social justice for all indonesian people will never be fulfilled because social justice cannot grow from offices and meetings must grow from the peoples foundation their villages before we talk about asset confiscation laws we must first create the container the vessel of fairness and that vessel is the village money barn chapter iii the rising equity every rupiah recovered from corruption every asset returned the state every fund restored the people must flow directly into the village money barns of indonesia that is how equality is born that is how fairness lives that is how the people finally smile again the village is the foundation of the republic every resource every tax every breath of labor comes from there sok power that does not serve the villages is not true power is arrogance disguised as authority the village money barn is not an idea is the heartbeat of peoples economy pumping life into true social justice final call from banyuwangi i edy mustaat son of banyuwangi and descendant of ponorogo badegan bandar alim call upon all leaders and thinkers of this land build the village money barns across indonesia let every tax every asset and every returned wealth flow back the peoples roots only then will justice descend from the constitution reality build the vessel first then share the harvest that vessel is the village money barn the sacred place where the truth of the peoples economy grows and shines freedom long live the village long live the people long live justice
